<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 6: CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND
        SLEEVES - CYLINDER SLEEVES - METHOD TWO
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>
            <emph type="underscr">METHOD TWO</emph>
        </title>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">"DIAL BORE GAUGE METHOD" (Refer to Figures
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600622">6.22</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600623">6.23</hotlnk>).
            </emph>
        </para>
        <para>Using a dial bore gauge (
            <emph type="bold">OEM1032</emph>):
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure at the top of the piston ring travel just below the carbon ridge area (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600622">6.22</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) and record the reading.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure below ring travel area (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600623">6.23</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) and record the reading.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>The difference between the two readings is the cylinder sleeve taper. If specifications are exceeded,
            replace sleeve.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef1600622" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg5337" filename="../figeg5/EG5337.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6.22 Measuring At The Top Of Cylinder Sleeve Piston Ring Travel Using Dial Bore Gauge
            </caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="ef1600623" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg5338" filename="../figeg5/EG5338.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6.23 Measuring Below Cylinder Sleeve Piston Ring Travel Using Dial Bore Gauge</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
